λ(gybis-arch-describe) ≡
├─ input:  architecture.md @ <root>/
├─ preflight: ¬initialized(architecture.md) ∨ empty(architecture.md)
│           → output("run /gybis-arch-init")
├─ step₁:  read(architecture.md, full)
├─ step₂:  translate → product_narrative {
│           │
│           ├─ what_is:     { problem_solved, users, user_needs }
│           ├─ what_can:    { capabilities, supported_needs, explicit_out_of_scope }
│           ├─ why_this_way: { principles_as_commitments, trade-offs, returns }
│           ├─ product_meaning: { extensible_points, constrained_points, quality_guarantees }
│           └─ system_cohesion: { moving_parts, connections, business_domain_language }
│         }
├─ step₃:  format → prose { light_headings, no_code, no_jargon, no_lambda_syntax, no_VSM_labels }
└─ output: product_manager_mental_model { direction, prioritization, trade-off_support }

key_constraints:
  ¬∃(lambda_expr ∨ technical_syntax ∨ VSM_layer_id) ∈ output
  ¬invented(capability) ∷ capability ⊆ architecture.md
  initialized(architecture.md) ? ¬suggest("/gybis-arch-init")
  rw(output) = false